WRITING.TEXT:
First I want to say that by going to the gym you will experience some failure and the most important thing is to not give up when it happens. My favorite quote is this: Success is not the absence of failure, but the persistance through it.
Everyone experience failure, it's just a matter of who deals with it better and correct themselves. I had couple of funny things happen to me while in the gym. One time I hadn't properly locked one of the leg machine handles and when I was doing my reps midway through it 100lbs of weight loudly dropped and everyone stared at me haha. It was unpleasant experience, but I told my mind that next time I will know how to use it and just forget what happened. You have to look at everyday as a great opportunity to learn new things and get more experienced.
When I first started I used any machine that I liked or previously saw people do on YouTube. Over 6 months I gained 12lbs of muscle. Personally I think I did a lot of progress not only physically, but also mentally and increased my self-esteem.
I would love to make you a week routine plan and explain you various exercises and machines, but I'm going to bed now and I'll contact you tomorrow. I'm also 20M
Edit: always keep that quote in mind, it helps!

Has anyone got any helpful tips for me?
Yes! I was in the exact same situation as you are right now. You are making the right desicion. Gym has helped me so much, I'm so happy that I made the commitment, and you will be too.
What I suggest you to do first is get to love fitness, get as much information about it as possible, so you are not a total noob at it, watch youtube videos on how to do certain exercises, how to use gym equipment properly, make your week routine plan, find your favorite youtube fitness channel. For me it was Hodgetwins, they were shy and skinny when they started working out and they've grown so much since then, they have funny personalities and are fun to watch and learn from.
Next thing is getting all that courage you have and going to sign up for the gym. I don't think I can give you any tips for how to do that better, you just have to really commit to it, get all that courage and just go there.
Fuck everybody else who may think something bad about you, that is their problem, not yours, you are a human being and you learn. Be courageous and DO IT! I'm rooting for you bro!
Edit: If you have any questions about gym or fitness, I would be happy to help you! AMA
